{
  "texts": [
    "LLM always gives the answer with the highest probability.",
    "If the sources are poor, this may lead to an accumulation of wrong answers.",
    "This was also evident in the first part of the analysis task which contained two trick questions.",
    "The correct answer to the question \"Which nations were also involved in the US air strike?\"",
    "was \"None, \" and the possible answer to the question \"What are the signs of a conventional explosion without the release of poison gas?\" was \"Nothing.\""
  ]
}